[4] Research
Date: 18 Jan 2019
Source: Journal of Infectious Diseases [edited]
https://academic.oup.com/jid/advance-article-abstract/doi/10.1093/infdis/jiz006/5292618?redirectedFrom=fulltext


Citation. Hayman DTS. Extensive serological survey of multiple African non-human primate species reveals low prevalence of IgG antibodies to four Ebola virus species. The Journal of Infectious Diseases, jiz006, https://doi.org/10.1093/infdis/jiz006

African primates: likely victims, not reservoirs, of ebolaviruses

Abstract
Bats are considered a reservoir species for Ebola viruses, but non-human primates (NHP) have represented a source of infection in several outbreaks in humans. Here we report serological screening of blood or fecal samples from monkeys (n=2322) and apes (n=2327). 36 NHP species from Cameroon, Democratic Republic of Congo and Ivory Coast were tested with a sensitive and specific Luminex-based assay for IgG antibodies to 4 Ebolavirus species. Using the simultaneous presence of antibodies to NP and GP proteins to define positivity, we showed that specific Ebola virus antibodies are not widespread among NHP. Only one mustached monkey (_Cercopithecus cephus_) from Cameroon was positive for Sudan Ebola virus. These observations support that NHP are most likely intermediate hosts for Ebola viruses. With the increasing frequency of Ebola outbreaks, it is crucial to identify the animal reservoir and understand the ecology of Ebola viruses to inform disease control.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall from Greg Folkers

[See Fausther-Bovendo H, Mulangu S, Sullivan NJ. 2012. Ebolavirus vaccines for humans and apes. Curr Opinion Virol 2 (3): 324-329.
https://doi.org/10.1016/j.coviro.2012.04.003

This paper discusses Ebola vaccines, not only for humans, but also considerations of potential ape vaccines to protect them from the devastating effects of Ebola on their populations. While they are intermediate hosts rather than reservoirs, Ebola virus is taking a great toll on endangered primates. - Mod.LK

